When the Beijing Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine was recruiting doctors in 2018 to offer medical care to athletes participating in the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics, Fu Yan, a doctor from Xiyuan Hospital of the China Academy of Chinese Medical Sciences signed up without hesitation. After more than three years of painstaking effort, Fu Yan has become a member of China's medical service team for the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics. She told CGTN that she's ready to impress the world as the first generation of Chinese ski doctor.